definition:
νηστεία, -ας, ἡ
 (νηστεύω), [in LXX for צוֹם ;] 
fasting, a fast; 
   (a) of voluntary abstinence from food: Mat.17:21 (WH, R, txt., om.), Mrk.9:29 (WH, txt., R, txt., om.), Luk.2:37, Act.14:23; of the Day of Atonement, Act.27:9; 
   (b) of involuntary abstinence: 2Co.6:5 11:27.†
 SYN.: ἀσιτία, q.v  (AS)
